{{Infobox organization |name = Officers Club, Dhaka |image = |image_border = |size = |alt = |caption = |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |abbreviation = |motto = |formation = 1967 |extinction = |type = |status = |purpose = |headquarters = [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]] |location = |coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> |region_served = Bangladesh |members = |language = Bengali |leader_title = |leader_name = |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = [http://officersclubdhaka.com/ Officers Club, Dhaka] |remarks = }}
'''Officers Club, Dhaka''' is a government officers club in [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Muhith: Everyone should pay tax|url=http://www.dhakatribune.com/business/2016/09/08/muhith-everyone-pay-tax/|website=dhakatribune.com|publisher=Dhaka Tribune|accessdate=27 September 2016|date=8 September 2016}}</ref> M Ibrahim Hossain Khan who is the additional Secretary of Public Administration Ministry was elected as General Secretary of the Club in 2016 with the term ending in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=Officers’ Club Dhaka gets new body|url=http://www.thefinancialexpress-bd.com/2016/01/16/10997|website=The Financial Express Online Version|accessdate=27 September 2016}}</ref> The club is described as being "exclusive".<ref>{{cite web|last1=Siddiqui|first1=Kamal|last2=Ahmed|first2=Jamshed|last3=Siddique|first3=Kaniz|last4=Huq|first4=Sayeedul|last5=Hossain|first5=Abul|last6=Nazimud-Doula|first6=Shah|last7=Rezawana|first7=Nahid|title=Social Formation in Dhaka, 1985–2005: A Longitudinal Study of Society in a Third World Megacity|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xqTeCwAAQBAJ&pg=PT424&dq=Officers%E2%80%99+Club,+Dhaka&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjzrK_eq67PAhUGzz4KHQUUAa0Q6AEIHjAA#v=onepage&q=Officers%E2%80%99%20Club%2C%20Dhaka&f=false|publisher=Routledge|accessdate=27 September 2016|language=en|date=1 April 2016}}</ref>
==History== The Club was founded in 1967. The club membership is restricted to government officers and officers of semi-government or autonomous bodies. The club is managed by an elected executive committee.<ref>{{cite web|title=Officers' Club Dhaka|url=http://officersclubdhaka.com/?page_id=148|website=officersclubdhaka.com|accessdate=27 September 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Officers’ Club, Dhaka|url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Officers%E2%80%99_Club,_Dhaka|website=en.banglapedia.org|publisher=Banglapedia|accessdate=27 September 2016}}</ref> The committee is elected for a term of two years.<ref>{{cite web|title=News Details|url=http://www.bssnews.net/newsDetails.php?cat=0&id=546900&date=2016-01-16|website=www.bssnews.net|accessdate=27 September 2016}}</ref>
